org.kohsuke.stapler.export

Interface DataWriter


  • public interface DataWriter
    Receives the event callback on the model data to be exposed.

    The call sequence is: 

     EVENTS := type? startObject PROPERTY* endObject
 PROPERTY := name VALUE
 VALUE := valuePrimitive
        | value
        | valueNull
        | startArray VALUE* endArray
        | EVENTS
    Author:
    Kohsuke Kawaguchi

      • type

        default void type(@Nullable
                  Type expected,
                  @Nullable
                  Class actual)
           throws IOException
        Augments the next startObject() call by specifying the type information of that object.
        Parameters:
        expected - The declared type of the variable that references this object. Null if the object is not referenced by anyone, for example when it's the root.
        actual - The actual type of the object being written. Null if the object is synthetic and has no valid Java type
        Throws:
        IOException
